# Target Allocation

> Your portfolio's intended composition.
> The agent compares your actual allocation to this and flags deviations > 5pp.
> Edit anytime; agent reads on each run.

## By bucket

| Bucket            | Target % | Notes |
|-------------------|----------|-------|
| US Large Tech     | 30       | Concentrated bet, AI cycle |
| US Other Equities | 25       | Broad market diversification |
| International     | 15       | Mostly developed markets, some EM |
| Bonds (LT)        | 10       | Duration exposure |
| Bonds (ST)        | 5        | Cash-alternative |
| Cash              | 15       | Dry powder for opportunities |
| **Total**         | **100**  |   |

## Rebalance rules

- **5pp deviation**: flag in the report
- **8pp deviation**: agent should explicitly recommend rebalancing
- **15pp deviation**: agent should mark this as urgent

## Individual position caps

No single position > 8% of total portfolio (let winners run, but not infinitely)
No single non-major position > 3% of total

## Style / tilt

- Quality bias: prefer companies with consistent FCF, healthy balance sheets
- Anti-meme: avoid hype-cycle names without numerical support
- Patience over precision: don't chase exact target allocation; rebalance quarterly unless urgent

---

_Edit freely. The agent reads this on every run. If the numbers don't add to 100, the agent will flag it._
